                        Rivetweb README
                        ---------------

 Rivetweb is a Tcl based engine for creating static template based websites.

 Rivetweb could useful if your goal is generation and update 
of small to medium size web sites bearing static content. Rivetweb maintains
strict separation between content, representation and structure of the web site,
it's template based, so you can easily change the XHTML/CSS code underlying
your pages and produce a whole entirely re-styled web site in seconds.

 Rivetweb is perfect when you have to create a website whose content is slowly
changing, for example when pages must provide structural information about 
working groups, small firms or technical documentation.  

 Rivetweb is not meant to run fast changing dynamic content. It's focused
on manageability and extensibility for HTML generation.

 Using Rivetweb with Apache's mod_rewrite you can let your 
dynamically generated pages appear as if every internal link is
is pointing to good old static .html files. Therefore you can fake
your website to be made out of only static HTML pages and generate an
entirely static copy of them for both on-line and off-line browsing

 As a consequence, by means of any mirror tool (e.g. wget) you can recreate a 
local copy of the website completely rewritten in .html files. This copy can 
be thus deployed with *any* webserver or even distributed on a Pendrive or 
a CD-ROM for offline browsing.

 A Rivetweb web site can be running several XHTML/CSS templates at the same 
time, you just switch from one to another by passing the 'template' parameter 
in the URL. This might be useful if you want to test different styles, 
compare them and let your customers decide which is best to their taste.

 Rivetweb is thought to be multilingual. Provided pages and other
resources are translated, the whole content can be served in multiple
languages. 

 Rivetweb is based on Rivet (http://tcl.apache.org/rivet/). Rivet is a
module and a Tcl programming suite for the Apache HTTP Webserver. 

Rivetweb is entirely free and released under BSD licence.

